method.name: count
method.shortdesc: Displays the number of elements in the UserDictionary.

method.name: item
method.shortdesc: Returns the UserDictionary with the specified index or name.

parameter.name: index
parameter.shortdesc: The index or name. Can accept: Long Integer or String.

method.name: itemByName
method.shortdesc: Returns the UserDictionary with the specified name.

method.name: itemByRange
method.shortdesc: Returns the UserDictionaries within the specified range.

parameter.name: from
parameter.shortdesc: The UserDictionary, index, or name at the beginning of the range. Can accept: UserDictionary, Long Integer or String.

parameter.name: to
parameter.shortdesc: The UserDictionary, index, or name at the end of the range. Can accept: UserDictionary, Long Integer or String.

method.name: firstItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the first UserDictionary in the collection.

method.name: lastItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the last UserDictionary in the collection.

method.name: middleItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the middle UserDictionary in the collection.

method.name: previousItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the UserDictionary with the index previous to the specified index.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The index of the UserDictionary that follows the desired UserDictionary.

method.name: nextItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the UserDictionary whose index follows the specified UserDictionary in the collection.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The UserDictionary whose index comes before the desired UserDictionary.

method.name: anyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns any UserDictionary in the collection.

method.name: everyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns every UserDictionary in the collection.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the UserDictionary.
Returns the UserDictionary with the specified index.
